Former president Jacob Zuma is fighting to have charges against him struck off the roll. • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. PIETERMARITZBURG - Former President Jacob Zuma's corruption trial enters its second day in the KwaZulu-Natal High Court in Pietermaritzburg. On Monday, Zuma's lawyers began their arguments for a permanent stay of prosecution. The former president is facing numerous charges, including racketeering, money laundering and corruption. READ: Zuma claims charges against him a 'political ploy' The charges relate to payments he allegedly received as a bribe to protect arms company Thales from an investigation into the controversial multibillion-rand arms deal. Zuma says he has evidence to prove his rights have been violated.